      "message": "PTAL\n\nThis is all necessary because we technically allow manifests like\n\n```\n@Subdir 1\nsome/pkg some:ver\n@Subdir 2\nsome/pkg some:ver\n@Subdir 3\nsome/pkg some:ver\n```\n\nSo when fetching stuff concurrently we must ensure not to fetch the same package multiple times (bad things may happen, especially when using \"temporary instance cache\" from https://chromium-review.googlesource.com/c/infra/luci/luci-go/+/2954704). \n\nNow all 3 concurrent fetches will get a pkg.Source backed by the exact same os.File object (still will unzip it multiple times, but it won\u0027t harm correctness and dedupping unzips will add a whole ton of complication, so I ignore it).",
